  <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Return & Cancel Policy</h2>

  <p>
    We aim to provide a smooth and fair return and refund experience for all our customers. Please review the following terms:
  </p>

  <ul >
    <li class="mt-3 mb-3"><strong>Cancellation:</strong> 
      Orders can only be cancelled <strong>before shipment</strong>. If the order is already shipped, cancellation is not possible.<br>
      Upon cancellation of a paid order, the <strong>full amount paid</strong> by the customer will be refunded to their <strong>BookD Wallet</strong>.
    </li>

    <li class="mt-3 mb-3"><strong>Returns:</strong> 
      Eligible books can be returned after delivery. The refund amount will be credited to your wallet.<br>
      <ul>
        <li class="mt-2 mb-2">Shipping charges are <strong>non-refundable</strong>, unless the return is due to our mistake (e.g., damaged or wrong book).</li>
        <li class="mt-2 mb-2">In such cases, contact customer care with valid proof. After review, the shipping charge may be refunded.</li>
        <li class="mt-2 mb-2">The rest of the amount paid by the customer (excluding shipping charges) will be refunded.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

   
    <li class="mt-3 mb-3"><strong>Important note in case of individual item return or cancellation from coupon-applied orders:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li class="mt-2 mb-2">Books priced below the applied coupon discount are <strong>not eligible</strong> for cancellation or return.</li>
        <li class="mt-2 mb-2">If cancelling or returning a book causes the order to <strong>violate the couponâ€™s minimum purchase condition</strong>, the full discount provided will be deducted from the refund of that item.
        Even <strong>if the coupon condition is still met,</strong> the <strong>proportional discount</strong> received for the specific book will be deducted from its refund amount.</li>
        
         <li class="mt-3 mb-3"><strong>Taxes:</strong> 
      Any proportional taxes on cancelled or returned items will be refunded as well.
    </li>
      </ul>
    </li>

   
  </ul>


